# .sanitize-patterns.example
#
# Template for the LOCAL, gitignored leak-pattern list used by
# scripts/sanitize-check.sh. Copy this file to `.sanitize-patterns.local`
# (which is gitignored) and replace the placeholders with YOUR real
# lab/tenant identifiers. The values you put here are PII/identifiers and
# must NEVER be committed — that is exactly why the live file is gitignored.
#
#   cp .sanitize-patterns.example .sanitize-patterns.local
#   $EDITOR .sanitize-patterns.local
#
# Format: one POSIX extended-regular-expression per line. Blank lines and
# lines starting with `#` are ignored. Escape regex metacharacters (`.`)
# and use `\b` word boundaries where helpful to avoid false positives.
#
# Add an entry for every identifier that ties content back to your tenant:

# --- DNS / domains ---
# example\.com

# --- People / UPNs / emails ---
# \bjdoe\b
# jdoe@example\.com

# --- Subscription / tenant / app UUID fragments (use a distinctive slice) ---
# 00000000-0000-0000-0000

# --- Resource groups / VNets / storage accounts ---
# rg-mylab\b
# vnet-mylab
# mystorageacct1234

# --- Internal / public IPs (RFC1918 ranges + any public IPs of your hosts) ---
# \b10\.0\.
# \b203\.0\.113\.10\b
